                        <mo>*</mo>
                    </msup>
                </math>
            </span>, which transitions 
        to its ground state with emission of one or more &#947;s. No A or Z 
        changes are involved in gamma decay. For example Co-60 decays to Ni-60 
        by &#946;, rapidly followed by two gammas of 1.173 MeV and 1.332 MeV energies.
        <br/><br/>
        &#947; rays are highly <strong>penetrating</strong> making them useful 
        medically, but also hazardous. Effective shielding requires a large 
        amount of mass, such as thick concrete walls. The main <strong>interaction 
        processes</strong> with matter (resulting in ionization and dose) are the
         photoelectric effect, Compton scattering, and pair production. 

